declarations.comments: All effects induced by a suggester during its lifespan.
declarations.title: SuggesterEffects

declarations.comments:
A suggester instance has a `send` function for providing new terms
and a subscribe function for listening for new suggestions.
The subscribe function will always be called with the most up to date
suggestions for the latest terms sent, even if a previous search is
slow to complete.  Subscribers immediately receive the most recent
result set.
declarations.title: SuggesterInstance

declarations.comments:
Create a suggester with the default API backend: Affjax.get & decodeJson,
no input debounce, and no input transformations.
declarations.title: mkSuggester

declarations.comments: Create a suggester with an alternate API backend.
declarations.title: mkSuggester'

declarations.comments:
Stores searched terms so they can be recalled without re-querying.
Also stores the current search terms.
declarations.title: SuggesterState

declarations.comments:
Updates the suggestion store, updating either
the current terms or search results.
declarations.title: updateSuggestions

declarations.comments:
Returns whether the store contains any form of results for the
current terms.
declarations.title: hasSuggestionResults

declarations.comments: Find the results for the store's current terms, or an empty result set.
declarations.title: getSuggestionResults

declarations.comments:
Any string.  Terms are normalized for searching. Ex:

"chevron scarves" will become "chevron-scarves" when passed to the API
declarations.title: Terms

declarations.comments:
A single suggestion row.  Phrase is the text which matched the search.
Hits represents relevancy (descending).
declarations.title: Suggestion

declarations.comments:
Suggestions are represented as a state and a collection of the
currently most relevant suggestions.  Ex:
```
Ready []
Loading []
Ready [a, b, c]
Loading [a, b, c] <- continue displaying these results until better ones are available
Ready [d, e, f]
```
declarations.title: Suggestions
